  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugees Fleeing Terror of ISIS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To save the lives of their children and families, the Yazidi families fled their homes to Northern Iraq (Kurdistan).  Now, they are living in empty containers, tents or abandoned buildings.   Some, while fleeing, experienced the murder of friends and family.  Many of the women and girls are suffering PTSD from the horror of rape (some as young as age 9) by ISIS militants.  GHNI teams are working to help families find safety, healing from trauma and the ability to rebuild lives.</narrative>
  </description>
